  So you want to amplify your TESes
=====================================

To create the hardware configuration file (mce.cfg), do the following:

1. Copy a template from the templates folder, e.g.

        cp templates/mce_v1.cin mce.cin


2. Modify the template as required (to change the TES configuration,
   or readout cards, or fast SQ2 switching settings).


3. Compile mce.cin into mce.cfg

        make mce.cfg


4. Install mce.cfg to /etc

        sudo make install

